senschaft, Kunstgeschichte und Pädagogikwird aufgezeigt, auf welche Weise sich die vielschichtigen Erfahrungen von Exil und Migration in Literatur und Kunst für Kinder und Jugendliche wiederfinden.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aExil. 4aJugendliteratur. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBannasch, Bettina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenner, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernstorff, Wiebke von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlumesberger, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBox, Marijke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDall’Armi, Julia von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDingelmaier, Theresia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDingelmaier, Theresia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDogramaci, Burcu, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDogramaci, Burcu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon Ginzburg, Etti, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeintz, Kathrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJagdschian, Larissa Carolin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKonrad, Anita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrüger, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuzminykh, Ksenia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaak, Jeannette van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeitloff, Isabelle, econtributor.4ctb4